## Read Before Acting

- Read `core/principles/development-principles.md` for the shared development principles used by all tools.
- Read `core/rules/token-efficiency.md` before broad exploration or repository scanning.
- Read `core/rules/maintainability.md` before planning or making code changes.
- Read `core/rules/model-routing.md` before deciding whether work belongs to a local model, cloud model, or human.
- Read `PROJECT_CONTEXT.md` for the project-specific architecture, stack, and constraints.
- Read `CODEMAP.md` before searching the repository for relevant files.
- Read `VERIFY.md` before implementing so verification commands are known upfront.

## Verification Commands

Use `VERIFY.md` as the source of truth for lint, test, build, and manual verification commands. If a command is missing or stale, update `VERIFY.md` as part of the change.

## AI Policy

Use `AI_POLICY.md` for project-specific boundaries: safe commands, forbidden operations, data handling rules, and when to stop for human review.

## Maintainability Constraints

Use `MAINTAINABILITY_NOTES.md` to identify the project-specific risks around architecture fit, coupling, naming, testability, error handling, and change cost.

## Skills Available

Codex consumes the same tool-neutral workflows as other adapters through `core/skills/`. For v0.1, the relevant workflow is `core/skills/idea-to-prepared-task/SKILL.md`, which turns a captured idea into a prepared task brief before cloud-model implementation.
